        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 8:21PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 821 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Collbran, or 25 miles east of Grand Junction,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mesa, Skyway, Plateau City, and Molina.

This includes Colorado 65 between mile markers 32 and 51.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
